Kisumu town is a hive of activity ahead of Madaraka Day celebrations on Tuesday.  Rehearsals by the Kenya Defence Forces and other entertainment groups were in top gear yesterday. Jet fighters and parachuters left many residents excited ahead of the celebrations.  The hospitality sector has recorded huge business with hotel bookings increasing despite restrictions on the number of people who will attend the event physically.  ODM leader Raila Odinga, Kisumu Governor Anyang' Nyong'o and Nyanza MPs flew to Kisumu soon after meeting with President Uhuru Kenyatta at State House in Nairobi on Friday.    Venue for Madaraka Day fete unknown as Kisumu Stadium left  Kenya-Burundi first ladies to conduct own business in Nyanza  Final touches as Kisumu readies to welcome Uhuru  Burundi President to attend Madaraka Day celebrations Raila drove to his Riat home where he reportedly met a few local leaders. Sources hinted that the President may visit the home.  The county government has deployed cleaners who are even washing the streets in readiness for the visitors, who include heads of government from the East African Community and diplomats.     Take a quick survey and help us improve our website!  Venue of Madaraka Day celebrations could be changed following fears of possible spike in Covid cases  Leaders from Nyanza region hold meeting with President Kenyatta ahead of Madaraka day celebrations  Walking down the memory lane of Nairobi city  By James Omoro | 13 hours ago By Kepher Otieno | 14 hours ago By Kepher Otieno | 17 hours ago By Kevine Omollo  | 21 hours ago Uhuru unveils major plans for Nyanza ahead of visit